## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

### Summary

**This is a textbook case of coverage-touching.** 10 test methods systematically call every public method on `ProductCatalog` but verify almost nothing. You hit 95% coverage because the code *executes*—not because correctness is *proven*.

| Severity | Count |
|----------|-------|
| Critical | 6 |
| High | 1 |
| Medium | 1 |

---

### 🔴 Critical — False Confidence

#### 1. Coverage Touching (Systemic)

The entire class follows the pattern: call method → no assertion (or trivial `IsNotNull`). Every method is "covered" but no behavior is verified.

**Affected tests with zero meaningful assertions:**

| Test | Problem | What could go wrong in prod undetected |
|------|---------|----------------------------------------|
| `AddProduct_Works` (L17) | No assertion at all | `Save()` could silently discard data |
| `UpdatePrice_Works` (L33) | No assertion | Price might not change, or could go negative |
| `RemoveProduct_Works` (L39) | No assertion | Product could remain in store |
| `GetProductCount_Works` (L63) | No assertion | Could return 0 or -1 and test still passes |
| `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` (L69) | No assertion | Discount could be applied wrong (e.g., `*fraction` instead of `*(1-fraction)`) |
| `ImportFromCsv_Works` (L85) | No assertion | Parsing could silently produce wrong Product records |

**Concrete fixes:**

```csharp
// AddProduct — verify the product is actually stored
[TestMethod]
public void AddProduct_StoresProductRetrievableBySku()
{
    var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);
    _catalog.AddProduct(product);
    var retrieved = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual("Widget", retrieved?.Name);
    Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, retrieved?.Price);
}

// UpdatePrice — verify the price actually changed
[TestMethod]
public void UpdatePrice_ChangesStoredPrice()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);
    var updated = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, updated?.Price);
}

// RemoveProduct — verify product is gone
[TestMethod]
public void RemoveProduct_MakesProductUnretrievable()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.RemoveProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.IsNull(_catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001"));
}

// GetProductCount — verify correct count
[TestMethod]
public void GetProductCount_ReturnsNumberOfStoredProducts()
